  The Ministry of Economic Planning, Budget and Development, Osun State, will today (Monday) commence a five-day retreat/capacity building workshop to craft a new 10-year State Development Plan (2018-2028). According to the ministry, the plan is aimed at creating a focus on how to achieve the development objectives and goals of the state with a view to improving the living conditions of Osun citizens in the next 10 years. It said in a statement signed by the Commissioner, Dr. Olalekan Yinusa, that the state development plan would enumerate Osunâ€™s overarching policy position and strategies for achieving the objectives.